⚡ Quick Start Guide
Prerequisites: MySQL 8.0+ and Node.js 18+

Bash
# 1. Clone the repository
git clone https://github.com/xan-antx/DBMS-Exam-Allocation-System.git
cd DBMS-Exam-Allocation-System

# 2. Import the database schema and sample data
mysql -u root -p < schema.sql

# 3. Configure the database
# Open db.js and insert your MySQL password

# 4. Install dependencies and run
npm install
node server.js
Access the live system at http://localhost:3000 via index.html.
